PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT

Project: Enterprise Financial Analytics Engine

Type: Resume & GitHub Portfolio Project

Architecture: Modular Financial ETL Pipeline

⸻

1. PROJECT GOAL

Build a modular financial data pipeline that:
	1.	Ingests structured financial transaction datasets.
	2.	Validates data quality and business rules.
	3.	Performs reconciliation between two financial sources.
	4.	Generates financial aggregates and variance analysis.
	5.	Produces reporting-ready SQL views.
	6.	Logs execution and reconciliation metrics.

The system must simulate enterprise-grade financial reporting architecture.

⸻

2. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE (LOGICAL FLOW)

Pipeline execution order:
	1.	Ingestion
	2.	Validation
	3.	Reconciliation
	4.	Aggregation
	5.	Reporting View Creation
	6.	Logging & Metrics Storage

Each stage must be modular and independently testable.

⸻

3. GLOBAL CONSTRAINTS
	•	Use Python for orchestration and logic.
	•	Use Snowflake as data warehouse.
	•	Use SQL for transformations and reporting views.
	•	No hardcoded credentials.
	•	Use environment variables (.env).
	•	All SQL must be parameterized.
	•	Follow schema separation:
	•	raw
	•	staging
	•	analytics
	•	logs

⸻

4. MODULE REQUIREMENTS

⸻

4.1 INGESTION MODULE

Objective

Load structured financial datasets into raw schema.

Inputs
	•	CSV file: bank_transactions.csv
	•	CSV file: ledger_transactions.csv
	•	CSV file (optional): budget_data.csv

Required Fields (Transactions)
	•	transaction_id
	•	transaction_date
	•	account_id
	•	amount
	•	transaction_type (debit/credit)
	•	source_system

Processing Requirements
	1.	Validate file exists.
	2.	Validate required columns.
	3.	Add ingestion_timestamp.
	4.	Insert into raw.raw_transactions table.
	5.	Log:
	•	record_count
	•	ingestion_time
	•	file_name

Output Tables

raw.raw_transactions

Failure Handling
	•	If schema mismatch → stop ingestion.
	•	Log error in logs.etl_run_logs.

⸻

4.2 VALIDATION MODULE

Objective

Ensure financial data integrity before reconciliation.

Validation Rules
	1.	No null values in:
	•	transaction_id
	•	amount
	•	transaction_date
	2.	transaction_id must be unique per source.
	3.	amount must be numeric.
	4.	transaction_type must be debit or credit.
	5.	transaction_date must be valid date format.
	6.	Debit/Credit balance check (optional simulation).

Processing Steps
	1.	Read from raw.raw_transactions.
	2.	Apply validation rules.
	3.	Split records into:
	•	valid_records
	•	rejected_records
	4.	Insert valid records into staging.validated_transactions.
	5.	Insert rejected records into staging.rejected_records.
	6.	Log validation summary.

Output Tables

staging.validated_transactions
staging.rejected_records

⸻

4.3 RECONCILIATION MODULE

Objective

Match transactions between bank and ledger sources.

Matching Types
	1.	Exact Match:
	•	transaction_id
	•	amount
	•	transaction_date
	2.	Tolerance-Based Match:
	•	amount difference ≤ configurable threshold

Configurable Parameter

tolerance_amount (default = 5.00)

Processing Steps
	1.	Separate validated records by source_system.
	2.	Perform exact match.
	3.	Remove matched rows from pool.
	4.	Perform tolerance-based match.
	5.	Identify unmatched records from both sources.
	6.	Compute reconciliation metrics:
	•	total_records
	•	matched_count
	•	unmatched_count
	•	match_rate_percentage

Output Tables

analytics.matched_transactions
analytics.unmatched_bank
analytics.unmatched_ledger
analytics.reconciliation_summary

⸻

4.4 AGGREGATION MODULE

Objective

Generate financial reporting aggregates.

Aggregation Types
	1.	Daily total amount per account.
	2.	Monthly total amount per account.
	3.	Debit vs Credit totals.
	4.	Account-level financial summary.

Variance Calculations

If budget_data available:
	1.	actual_amount
	2.	budget_amount
	3.	variance_amount = actual - budget
	4.	variance_percentage

Output Tables

analytics.daily_summary
analytics.monthly_summary
analytics.variance_analysis

⸻

4.5 REPORTING MODULE

Objective

Create reporting-ready SQL views.

Required Views

analytics.v_financial_summary
analytics.v_reconciliation_summary
analytics.v_variance_summary

Views must:
	•	Aggregate relevant fields
	•	Be query-ready
	•	Not expose raw schema

⸻

4.6 LOGGING & MONITORING MODULE

Objective

Track pipeline execution and governance.

For Each Run:

Generate:
	•	run_id (UUID)
	•	start_time
	•	end_time
	•	total_ingested
	•	total_validated
	•	total_matched
	•	match_rate
	•	status (SUCCESS/FAILED)

Insert into:

logs.etl_run_logs

Security Requirement

Logs must not expose credentials or sensitive values.

